data.description: What a wonderful opportunity to own in a highly desirable neighborhood.  This 6 bedroom, 3.5 bathroom two story brick home has plenty of living space including a cozy living room with gas fireplace, formal dining room, sun room, and partially finished basement with an additional 7th non conforming en suite bedroom!  The master suite is on the main level and has a large walk in closet with doors at both ends for plenty of storage.  The home has many nice features such as Geothermal heating and cooling,  a newer 30 yr roof, newer Parco replacement vinyl windows that have a lifetime warrantee which is transferable, a Rain Soft Reverse Osmosis System, and some Kasa smart switches.  The home is filled with lovely oak trim, solid wood doors and built in cabinets.  The rocking chair covered front deck is the perfect spot to enjoy the day.  The sunroom with heated floors opens to a nice patio inside the fenced back yard.  The large 3 car garage allows for plenty of space and a workshop.  Don't miss out on this gorgeous property!  Call for your personal showing.
